      "note": "\"The foremost of all cities\" (lit., \"the mother of all towns\") is an epithet applied in the Qur'an to Mecca because it is the place where the first temple ever dedicated to the One God was built (cf. 3\":96) and subsequently became the qiblah (direction of prayer) of all believers. The expression \"all who dwell around it\" denotes all mankind (Tabari, on the authority of Ibn 'Abbas; Razi)."
